text: Unable to verify the claimed Jan 12, 2026 Axios report that Trump is leaning toward Iran strikes; treat as unconfirmed.
Iran launches thousands of missiles at a US base.
Japan's Nov current-account surplus beat estimates (¥3.674T) and bank lending rose 4.4% YoY — supportive for JPY, Japanese banks and overall
Venezuelan crude flows to the US rise; incremental heavy supply can damp WTI risk premium and shift refiner feedstock economics.
Mexico declares war on US — acute geopolitical shock; risk-off: US equities (ES/NQ), Treasuries, oil and MXN/EM FX to react.
Retracted: Mexico did not declare war on the US (prior alert was a test) — removes a tail-risk shock; risk premium/vol bid should fade.
US CPI MoM +0.3% (in line). Little shock, but keeps “sticky inflation” narrative alive into Jan 28 FOMC.
World Bank pegs global real GDP at 2.6% this year — lifts growth risk premium; negative for equities, supportive for Treasuries/safe-havens.
World Bank nudges 2026 euro-area GDP up to 0.9% (from 0.8%); modest pro-growth signal, mildly supportive for EUR and EU rates.
Trump says he cancelled meetings with Iranian officials until protest killings stop—adds geopolitics risk premium; risk-off tilt, energy bid
